  <bioghist id="aspace_3c3f0d4db1ad0dcbeeb71dc62be48033">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>Henry Phelps Gage was a physicist and inventor, and son of Cornell University Professor Simon Henry Gage and Susanna Phelps Gage, also a scientist.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_d2243a3506bf28f7dc3af33f6bebf289">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Correspondence, diaries, notes on the life of Simon Henry Gage; notebooks on lectures at Ithaca High School and Cornell University; printed matter on physics and related subjects; slides, photos, photographic plates, and miscellaneous papers. Includes correspondence and other papers pertaining to Henry Phelps Gage's work as head of the Optical Laboratory of Corning Glass Works (1911-1947) and to his membership in various scientific societies; also personal and family correspondence, including papers of Susanna Phelps Gage.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <prefercite id="aspace_fe64a6165bbc4f7e7c2d4d953cadbf0b">
    <head>Cite As:</head>
<p>Henry Phelps Gage papers, #1874. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.</p>  </prefercite>
